Class ArrowType

java.lang.Object
  de.unisiegen.tpml.core.types.Type
      de.unisiegen.tpml.core.types.MonoType
          de.unisiegen.tpml.core.types.ArrowType
All Implemented Interfaces:
PrettyPrintable, PrettyPrintPriorities
public final class ArrowType
extends MonoType

This class represents function types (so called arrow types) in our type systems. Arrow types are composed of two types, the parameter type tau1 and the result type tau2, both monomorphic types.

Version:
$Rev: 420 $
Author:
Benedikt Meurer
See Also:
BooleanType, IntegerType, MonoType

free

public TreeSet<TypeVariable> free()
Returns the set of free type variables present within this type. The default implementation simply returns the empty set, and derived classes will need to override this method to return the set of free type variables. The returned set should be considered read-only by the caller and must not be modified.

Overrides:
free in class Type

the set of free type variables within this type.
